<http://dx.doi.org/10.1163/18759866-BJA10013>
    dc:creator "Jeratthitikul, Ekgachai", "Panha, Somsak", "Pholyotha, Arthit", "Sutcharit, Chirasak", "Tongkerd, Piyoros" ;
    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "Integrative systematics reveals the new land-snail genus Taphrenalla (Eupulmonata: Ariophantidae) with a description of nine new species from Thailand" ;
    bibo:endPage "69" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Contributions to Zoology" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2020-12-07" ;
    bibo:startPage "21" ;
    bibo:volume "90" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8343291>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8343293>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8343295>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8355695> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8343291>
    dc:description "Figure 1 Map showing the sampling sites of the 11 Taphrenalla species along Southern Thailand.Each colour of the distribution range follows the phylogenetic tree of all Taphrenalla species in fig.3." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8343291/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8343293>
    dc:description "Figure 2 Representative ML tree of the Taphrenalla gen.nov., Macrochlamys, Sarika, Cryptozona, Hemiplecta, Megaustenia, and Durgella based on the combined partial sequences of the COI, 16S, and 28S genes. The code in the parenthesis next to the species name refers to voucher numbers of the analysed samples.Numbers on the branches indicate the ML BS and BI PP values." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8343293/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8343295>
    dc:description "Figure 3 A representative ML tree showing only the Taphrenalla clade.The synopsis of the radial groove on shell sculpture, genitalia showing location of dart apparatus, and live specimens of Taphrenalla spp. Results of species delimitation analyses based on the COI gene using ABGD and PTP.Black circles represent nodes with both ML (when Ē 70%) and BI (when Ē 0.95) support.White circles represent nodes with ML BS support but no BI PP support (when <0.95). Each clade colour refers to the distribution range in fig. 1." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8343295/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8355695>
    dc:description "Figure 8 Shells.A–C.Taphrenalla diadema. A.specimen CUMZ 7175.B. specimen CUMZ 7177.C.specimen CUMZ 7171 showing channel-shaped suture with wide bottom.D, E.T.dalli sp. nov. D. holotype CUMZ 7183.E. specimen CUMZ 7189 showing channel-shaped suture with very wide bottom. Inset SEM image showing shell sculpture of each species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8355695/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

